The paper deals with the capacity of group testing problems, which involves information theory and communication channels, suggesting a strong connection to the Information Theory (cs.IT) category. The paper also involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), as well as combinatorial optimization and discrete mathematics (cs.DM), which are relevant to the study of group testing. The paper also discusses noisy models and performance analysis, which are related to the fields of signal processing and machine learning, suggesting a possible connection to the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories.
